  A Limpopo girl who had an argument
with her stepdad, allegedly stabbed and killed him with a knife on Sunday
evening. The Limpopo police spokesman
Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said police are still investigating. "We currently do not know why the teenage
girl killed her stepdad," Mojapelo said. Mojapelo confirmed that the girl is
now behind bars and is expected to appear before the Namakgale Magistrate's
court soon. The girl, her mom and 41-year-old stepdad
stayed at the RDP Section in Namakgale outside Phalaborwa. "It was at about 19:40 when
our police received a call about the murder. Upon our arrival at the scene, the
body of the deceased was found lying on the floor," said Mojapelo. Mojapelo said the stepdad was
stabbed in the upper body.